Reasoning: The paper presents an algorithm for automated problem identification in supervised learning, specifically for identifying whether a dataset represents a regression or classification problem. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the core concepts and techniques of machine learning. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers the broader field of AI, which includes machine learning. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the proposed algorithm uses an evolutionary algorithm interface to TensorFlow to manipulate a deep neural network. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible categories as the paper mentions testing the algorithm on sentiment analysis datasets and recommends a neural network architecture.
